info.name: Minecraft End Portal Animation
info.description:
My take on the "End" shader from minecraft.

originale(procedural) version y EmmaChase in 2021-02-05
https://www.shadertoy.com/view/wtdfDn

renderpass.code:
/*

Here is how to loads the texture needed for this shader:
 - Open the javascript console of your browser:
				   Mac      /     Windows
	Chrome:  cmd + opt + J  /  ctrl + shift J
	Firefox: cmd + opt + K  /  ctrl + shift K
    IE:          na         /  F12   

- Then copy the following lines in the console to load custom texture:

gShaderToy.SetTexture(0, {mSrc:'data:image/jpeg;base64,', mType:'texture', mID:1, mSampler:{ filter: 'nearest', wrap: 'repeat', vflip:'true', srgb:'false', internal:'byte' }});


*/

/* VARIABLES */
#define ZOOM 1.0
#define SPEED 0.002
#define LIGHT 1.4

/* CONST */
#define PI   3.14159265359
#define PI2  1.57079632679
#define PI4  0.78539816339
#define PI6  0.52359877559
#define PI8  0.39269908169
#define PI16 0.19634954084
#define PI32 0.09817477042

mat2 rotate2d(float _angle){
    return mat2(
        cos(_angle),-sin(_angle),
        sin(_angle),cos(_angle)
    );
}


vec4 render_pic_layer(vec2 fragCoord, vec3 color, float direction, float scale )
{
  vec2 size_image = vec2(ZOOM*scale, ZOOM*scale);
  vec2 uv = fragCoord/size_image; // Normalized pixel coordinates (from 0 to 1)
  
  uv *= rotate2d(direction);
  uv += vec2(0.0,-1.0) * SPEED * scale * iTime;
  
  vec4 col = texture(iChannel0, uv);

  return vec4(col) * vec4(color, 1.0); // Output to screen
}



void mainImage( out vec4 fragColor, in vec2 fragCoord )
{
    fragColor = vec4(0.0, 0.0, 0.0, 1.0);
    fragCoord /= iResolution.xy;
    fragCoord.x *= iResolution.x/iResolution.y;

    fragColor += render_pic_layer(fragCoord, vec3(0.09, 0.22, 0.44), PI2+PI32, 2.2);
    fragColor += render_pic_layer(fragCoord, vec3(0.20, 0.28, 0.29), PI-PI8, 1.3);
    fragColor += render_pic_layer(fragCoord, vec3(0.07, 0.20, 0.21), PI +1.0*PI4, 1.0);
    fragColor += render_pic_layer(fragCoord, vec3(0.16, 0.17, 0.20), PI16, 0.8);
    
    fragColor += render_pic_layer(fragCoord, vec3(0.16, 0.13, 0.18), -PI4, 0.9);
    fragColor += render_pic_layer(fragCoord, vec3(0.16, 0.13, 0.18), PI2-PI6, 0.3);
    fragColor += render_pic_layer(fragCoord, vec3(0.16, 0.13, 0.18), PI32, 0.2);
    fragColor += render_pic_layer(fragCoord, vec3(0.16, 0.13, 0.18), PI, 0.1);
    
    fragColor *= LIGHT;
}
renderpass.name: Image
